ning of the satellite distribution\nhave a frequency of <0.1 per cent for any number of k > 3 combined orbital\npoles, indicating that these results are not affected by a look-elsewhere\neffect. This compounds the Planes of Satellite Galaxies Problem.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Nov 2019 19:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-08"}
